{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17651260","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17651260"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:21:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:21:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18438"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18438","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18438"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11156"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74720"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11156","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11156"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18438"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60204"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4948"},{"type":"tags","id":"7759"},{"type":"tags","id":"7761"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25865"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25872"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74720","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74720"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA researcher is investigating the effects of three different fertiliser types on plant growth. They randomly assign 60 tomato plants to one of three groups: organic fertiliser, synthetic fertiliser, or combined approach. After 12 weeks, they measure the height (cm) of each plant.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statistical tests is most appropriate for comparing the mean plant heights between these three groups?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Chi-square test","Wilcoxon signed-rank test","Paired t-test","One-way ANOVA","Simple linear regression"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eone-way ANOVA\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate test for this scenario as it compares means between three or more independent groups. ANOVA tests the null hypothesis that all group means are equal by comparing the variance between groups to the variance within groups. If the ANOVA result is significant, post-hoc tests would then be needed to determine which specific groups differ from each other.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other tests are inappropriate because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPaired t-test \u003C/strong\u003Eand \u003Cstrong\u003EWilcoxon signed-rank test \u003C/strong\u003Eare parametric and non-parametric tests, respectively, that can be used to compare two related measurements on the same subjects, not independent groups\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChi-square test\u003C/strong\u003E is used for categorical data, not continuous measurements like plant height\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESimple linear regression\u003C/strong\u003E analyses the relationship between two continuous variables, not group differences.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Analysis of variance (ANOVA) tests for differences between means of three or more independent groups.","ANOVA produces an F-statistic by comparing between-group variance to within-group variance.","A significant ANOVA result indicates that at least one group mean differs from the others, but does not specify which groups differ."],"references":["Sullivan LM. Essentials of biostatistics in public health. 3rd ed. Burlington (MA): Jones \u0026 Bartlett Learning; 2018.","Dawson B, Trapp RG. Basic \u0026 clinical biostatistics. 4th ed. New York: McGraw-Hill; 2004."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60204"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18438"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60204","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60204"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-26T16:10:32+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-26T16:12:27+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11156"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74720"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/76"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level II","synonyms":null,"description":"Understand (interpreting and summarizing information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4948","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4948"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udcca","name":"Biostatistics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T13:30:29+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"14"}},"heading":{"data":null}}